251.810","u": "Well, go on."},    {"who": "Ilmar A.", "start": "1253.612","u": "Then I went to . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1256.326","u": "Did the Germans beat you at any time?"},    {"who": "Ilmar A.", "start": "1260.072","u": "No, I personally was never beaten."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1263.148","u": "Why not? Did they beat anybody else?"},    {"who": "Ilmar A.", "start": "1266.319","u": "I saw that, but me, they never, no."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1269.609","u": "And who were the people whom they did beat?"},    {"who": "Ilmar A.", "start": "1273.811","u": "This I cannot say. I do not know what nationality or what they have, they were, uh, of many nationalities, Lets, Lithuanians, Poles, all sorts of people."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1288.143","u": "Well, go on. Did you go to the countryside?"},    {"who": "Ilmar A.", "start": "1291.274","u": "And I was in the countryside and I worked there until, uh, May 5, 1945."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1302.123","u": "What happened then? (One moment.) [Boder as if talking to someone in the background]. How did the farmer behave toward you? Did he give you enough to eat?"},    {"who": "Ilmar A.", "start": "1309.659","u": "Enough food he did not give, but I ate separately."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1316.044","u": "What does that mean, you &#34;ate separately&#34;?"},    {"who": "Ilmar A.", "start": "1316.926","u": "Ate extra in, in a room and the farmer ate in the dining room."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1330.073","u": "And what did they [no verb] you, [corrects himself] and did they pay you anything?"},    {"who": "Ilmar A.", "start": "1336.875","u": "There they paid us twenty-three marks per month."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1341.256","u": "And who was with you?"},    {"who": "Ilmar A.", "start": "1344.089","u": "I beg your pardon?"},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1345.133","u": "You say &#34;us,&#34; who was there with you?"},    {"who": "Ilmar A.", "start": "1348.284","u": "Well, I meant that, uh, . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1351.018","u": ". . . in general?"},    {"who": "Ilmar A.", "start": "1351.689","u": ". . . in general, [unintelligible]."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1353.352","u": "Twenty-three marks per month. And what was there to buy with twenty-three marks?"},    {"who": "Ilmar A.", "start": "1358.765","u": "For the money, you could not buy anything."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1362.908","u": "Did you have a ration card?"},    {"who": "Ilmar A.", "start": "1364.745","u": "No, I did not have. Instead, the farmer gave me. Gave food."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1369.324","u": "Gave food. How did the farmer, how did the farmer behave? Was he decent? Was he friendly?"},    {"who": "Ilmar A.", "start": "1378.070","u": "At first, he was not friendly. But in the end I worked well, because I am a young man after all, and the farmer was quite decent."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1393.602","u": "Well. And what happened on May 5, that&#39;s what you said, right, March 5 [sic], what happened then? What was that?"},    {"who": "Ilmar A.", "start": "1399.626","u": "Then the American occupation troops arrived and we were freed from the Germans, and we could be supplied for by the Americans."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1411.448","u": "Where was that? Was that in . . . ?"},    {"who": "Ilmar A.", "start": "1413.012","u": "That was in Oberlungwitz, that was . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1414.870","u": "Is that in the American Zone?"},    {"who": "Ilmar A.", "start": "1416.592","u": "No, this is not in the American Zone now, it is now the Russian Zone."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1422.104","u": "It is the Russian Zone?"},    {"who": "Ilmar A.", "start": "1423.195","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1423.945","u": "And, did you get from that zone to here, to Munich?"},    {"who": "Ilmar A.", "start": "1428.505","u": "I flee&#226;, I fled from that zone again."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1434.473","u": "Why?"},    {"who": "Ilmar A.", "start": "1435.342","u": "That is because I heard that the Russians would be coming there. And I was afraid already because I flee already from the Russians in 1944 and I know what that means; that was . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1451.886","u": "[interrupts] In &#39;44 you were not fleeing from the Russians, were you? &#39;44 you were fleeing from the Germans, right?"},    {"who": "Ilmar A.", "start": "1455.945","u": "From the Germans and here as well from the Russians."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1457.846","u": "Oh, that the Russians are coming, yes."},    {"who": "Ilmar A.", "start": "1457.846","u": "The Russians were coming and I know what it means, a Russian occupation because, that, uh, in 1941, on the 14th July one was, were deported sixty thousand men and women to Siberia. Sixty thousand of us."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1477.015","u": "Sixteen?"},    {"who": "Ilmar A.", "start": "1477.606","u": "Sixty."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1478.495","u": "Sixty-thousand."},    {"who": "Ilmar A.", "start": "1479.047","u": "Yes. That means, uh, one, uh, seven percent . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1488.583","u": "Yes, of the whole."},    {"who": "Ilmar A.", "start": "1489.460","u": "of the whole population."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1491.662","u": "Well? [short break in the recording] What happened there?"},    {"who": "Ilmar A.", "start": "1504.254","u": "Here I lived and I wanted to go on with my studies and I asked to be given the chance to continue studying somewhere in Germany. Now I have heard that . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1524.012","u": "Yes?"},    {"who": "Ilmar A.", "start": "1524.504","u": ". . . I heard that here in Munich is, founds a UNRRA University, that is an international university where there are studying nineteen, twelve . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1535.171","u": "I see. What are you studying here?"},    {"who": "Ilmar A.", "start": "1537.449","u": "I am studying &#34;Bauwesen&#34; [Building or construction]."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1539.092","u": "What? &#34;Bauwesen&#34;?"},    {"who": "Ilmar A.", "start": "1540.021","u": "&#34;Bauwesen.&#34;"},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1540.513","u": "Architecture?"},    {"who": "Ilmar A.", "start": "1540.926","u": "Archi&#226;, no, not archi&#226;, but subject area &#34;Bauwesen.&#34;"},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1544.871","u": "Well, building houses?"},    {"who": "Ilmar A.", "start": "1546.752","u": "Houses, &#34;Tief- und Hochbau.&#34;"},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1548.812","u": "What means &#34;Tiefbau&#34;?"},    {"who": "Ilmar A.", "start": "1550.473","u": "That, also hydraulic engineering, uh, and canals, channels, and [unintelligible] and so forth."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1556.313","u": "I see, and how long is that going to take?"},    {"who": "Ilmar A.", "start": "1560.138","u": "Here in Germany it will take three years. We have tri-semesters, we have three semesters a year."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1566.274","u": "Yes. And what is the language of instruction?"},    {"who": "Ilmar A.", "start": "1569.211","u": "Instruction is in the German language."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1572.074","u": "Now, tell me. Where do you think of going from here? Are you hearing word from your parents? What happened with your parents?"},    {"who": "Ilmar A.", "start": "1579.523","u": "I have not heard from my parents, that is because we have no connection. In my opinion, my parents have already been deported to Siberia. That is probable."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "1593.760","u": "And what are the people doing when they are deported to Siberia?"},    {"who": "Ilmar A.", "start": "1597.486","u": "They are,